WEBVTT

00:11.409 --> 00:12.875
It's cleanliness
everywhere I look.

00:12.877 --> 00:14.493
It's very
disorientating.

00:14.495 --> 00:17.947
Don't worry, I did not
touch your wall of crazy.

00:17.949 --> 00:19.915
The idea that Irene was murdered

00:19.917 --> 00:22.751
by a shadowy kingpin that no
one's ever seen or heard of

00:22.753 --> 00:24.086
sounded crazy
to me, too.

00:24.088 --> 00:26.589
But there may be
a pattern here.

00:26.591 --> 00:29.542
A trail of bread crumbs that
leads to a great criminal mind.

00:29.544 --> 00:32.293
And how is
Napoleon Bonaparte involved?

00:32.296 --> 00:35.264
By my fifth night without
sleep, I may have been reaching.

00:35.266 --> 00:37.132
What time is it?

00:37.134 --> 00:38.634
Uh, it's 9:30.

00:38.636 --> 00:40.102
Wednesday.

00:40.104 --> 00:42.638
You slept for
two days straight.

00:42.640 --> 00:44.590
That's why I'm so hungry.

00:44.592 --> 00:46.925
I'm supposed to go out
for a little while,

00:46.927 --> 00:49.278
but if you're still
feeling obsessed, I can stay.

00:49.280 --> 00:50.946
No, I'm fine.

00:50.948 --> 00:52.648
I've been
neglecting my hobby.

00:52.650 --> 00:55.284
I'm going to visit
Swirl-Theory.com

00:55.286 --> 00:57.620
and discuss
conspiracy theories.

00:57.622 --> 00:59.271
Your hobby is
conspiracy theories?

00:59.273 --> 01:00.539
No, of course not.

01:00.541 --> 01:01.957
They're pure sophistry.

01:01.959 --> 01:04.108
Large groups of people
cannot keep secrets.

01:04.111 --> 01:06.545
My hobby is
conspiracy <i>theorists.</i>

01:06.547 --> 01:07.630
I adore them.

01:07.632 --> 01:10.049
As one would
a barmy uncle.

01:10.051 --> 01:11.884
Or a pet that can't stop
walking into walls.

01:11.886 --> 01:14.386
Have you ever heard anyone say
the CIA invented crack cocaine?

01:14.388 --> 01:15.638
I have.

01:15.640 --> 01:16.805
I started that.

01:16.807 --> 01:17.890
That's ridiculous.

01:17.892 --> 01:19.291
Mm.

01:19.293 --> 01:21.727
Today, I plan to get
in touch with Zapruder--

01:21.729 --> 01:23.646
that's the moderator's
nom de plume--

01:23.648 --> 01:26.482
and share with him the results
of a secret government study,

01:26.484 --> 01:28.300
which concludes that
rising ocean waters

01:28.302 --> 01:32.137
will soon make a new coastline
in the Appalachian foothills.

01:32.139 --> 01:34.490
Plans are afoot to move
the nation's capital to Omaha,

01:34.492 --> 01:36.158
and a cadre of
elite billionaires

01:36.160 --> 01:38.327
is buying up soon-to-be
beachfront property.

01:39.480 --> 01:41.413
Okay, well, good
luck with that.

01:41.415 --> 01:44.500
Mm. Enjoy your errands.

01:45.585 --> 01:47.753
<i>Sherlock has made progress,</i>

01:47.755 --> 01:49.672
but he's fragile.

01:49.674 --> 01:53.092
Sebastian Moran upset
the balance that we found.

01:53.094 --> 01:56.462
He's finally ready to deal
with his feelings about Irene.

01:56.464 --> 01:58.614
He's only loved one person
in his life,

01:58.616 --> 02:00.833
as far as I can tell,
and she was murdered.

02:00.835 --> 02:03.335
Your contract to work as
Sherlock's sober companion

02:03.337 --> 02:04.836
expired a week ago.

02:04.838 --> 02:06.872
And if Sherlock
finds out,

02:06.874 --> 02:09.091
it could destroy the
trust you've built.

02:10.827 --> 02:12.695
Have you considered
that you yourself

02:12.697 --> 02:15.064
could be the catalyst
for a relapse?

02:15.066 --> 02:16.682
It's not forever.

02:16.684 --> 02:20.035
It may not be forever,
but it does sound indefinite.

02:20.037 --> 02:22.521
In the meantime,
you're not being paid.

02:22.523 --> 02:23.689
I'm not living
paycheck to paycheck.

02:23.691 --> 02:25.040
Nor are you obligated

02:25.042 --> 02:27.910
to spend your savings
on behalf of someone

02:27.912 --> 02:29.712
who's no longer your client.

02:31.365 --> 02:33.799
I should really check to see
if everything's okay.

02:40.257 --> 02:42.675
This thing with-with Sherlock,

02:42.677 --> 02:45.210
there are steps.

02:45.212 --> 02:47.563
Captain Gregson
suspended him from the NYPD.

02:47.565 --> 02:49.881
That relationship
stabilizes him.

02:49.883 --> 02:54.319
I just need to reopen that line
of communication between them.

03:00.243 --> 03:02.077
Watson.

03:02.079 --> 03:03.759
You want to tell me
whose house this is?

03:03.784 --> 03:04.664
Zapruder.

03:04.665 --> 03:07.032
Oh. Is that the guy you were
talking about this morning?

03:07.034 --> 03:08.233
The conspiracy theorist.

03:08.235 --> 03:10.068
His real name is
Len Pontecorvo.

03:10.070 --> 03:11.754
He didn't rise to
my bait earlier.

03:11.756 --> 03:13.355
Most unlike the man.

03:13.357 --> 03:15.090
I e-mailed several of his
colleagues in Swirl Theory.

03:15.092 --> 03:17.242
Turns out, no one has heard
from him since Sunday.

03:17.244 --> 03:19.094
Oh, so you decided to
break into his house?

03:19.096 --> 03:20.763
Well, his compatriots
feared the worst:

03:20.765 --> 03:22.431
black-bagged
by the KGB,

03:22.433 --> 03:24.249
taken to a secret
NASA prison.

03:24.251 --> 03:25.884
Please don't tell
me you agree.

03:25.886 --> 03:27.436
Of course not.
NASA doesn't maintain prisons.

03:27.438 --> 03:29.188
Everyone knows that.

03:29.190 --> 03:32.975
But I did think he may have had
a heart attack or an accident.

03:32.977 --> 03:36.061
Which is why I let myself in
when he didn't answer his door.

03:36.063 --> 03:38.597
This thing we're doing right
now, it's called trespassing.

03:38.599 --> 03:39.815
Well, if you're worried
about Mr. Pontecorvo

03:39.817 --> 03:41.700
pressing charges,
you shouldn't be.

03:41.702 --> 03:44.953
He's got much larger
problems than us.

03:46.607 --> 03:50.607
